# React Native Frontend Rules

## Stack
- Expo + React Native + TypeScript strict. Web is the primary target (react-native-web); iOS must still compile.
- Navigation: expo-router (file-based). Styling: NativeWind. State: Zustand (light) + TanStack Query for server state. No Redux.

## Platform safety
- Never use `document`, `window`, `localStorage` directly. Platform-specific code goes in `Component.web.tsx` / `Component.native.tsx` pairs.
- Video/audio playback: `expo-av` (works web+native). The pseudo-player advances scenes on the audio `didJustFinish` status, not on timers.

## Structure
- `app/(auth)/` sign-in, sign-up. `app/(tabs)/profile.tsx` is the default route.
- Feature folders: `src/features/<name>/{components,hooks,api}.`
- API layer: all HTTP in `src/api/`; components never call fetch directly. Mocks in `src/api/mocks/` mirror real client signatures 1:1 so integration is a one-line import swap.

## UI standards
- Every screen implements 4 states: loading / empty / error / success. Error states include a retry action.
- Catalogue selections (topics, interests) are multi-select chip grids from a static catalogue constant — never free-text.
- Analytics widgets (time spent, peak hours, most-watched topic) render from a single `/analytics/summary` response; no client-side aggregation of raw events.
- Track watch time by posting heartbeat events every 10s of playback: `{videoId, topicId, secondsWatched}`.

## Quality gates
- `tsc --noEmit` must pass before any commit. No `any`, no `@ts-ignore` without a comment.
- Components > 150 lines must be split. Hooks own logic; components own layout.
